  <Fragment slot="extra-sections">
    <section>
      <h2>Pick your method by the cup you want</h2>
      <p>If you keep hopping from one AeroPress recipe to another, stop thinking in terms of “best recipe ever” and start thinking in terms of cup goal. Do you want brightness? More body? A stronger base for milk? A travel method that still tastes like coffee instead of compromise? Once you answer that, the method usually gets pretty obvious.</p>
      <p>The other trap is changing three things at once. That is how perfectly good brewers end up getting blamed for bad cups. Keep the dose steady, keep the water steady, then change one variable. AeroPress rewards boring discipline more than clever chaos.</p>

      <PickOne
